radiographic_examinations.findings: A new 8-mm nonpalpable mass with lobulated margins detected in the lower inner retroareolar region of the left breast.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: The mass was thought to be a new primary cancer based on the different hormone receptor profile, absence of circumscribed margins, and previous cancer characteristics.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Baseline mammograms showed no significant findings except for the noncancerous lymph nodes, which remained unchanged.
